Therefore, if the policy had a flag, it was treated with an additional level of 1 for the policy while the maximum value was also increased by 1. To rescale all policies into values ranging from 0 to 100, the possible maximum value of each policy should be calculated beforehand. Thus, we set the maximum value as (maximum ordinal scale) + 1 to consider the flag for policies with flag information. If a policy has a flag, it was treated with an additional level of 1 for the strictness of the policy. For example, E1 has the ordinal scale of 0, 1, 2 but since it has a flag, its maximum value was calculated as 3.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
